NewEntity.Name: Animal
NewEntity.Description: Livestock - domestic farm animals kept for productive purposes (meat, milk, work, wool)

Columns.Name: AnimalId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an animal.

Columns.Name: AnimalName
Columns.Description: The name of the animal.

Columns.Name: AnimalDescription
Columns.Description: The description of the animal.

Columns.Name: AnimalDataOfBirth
Columns.Description: The date of birth of the animal.

Columns.Name: AnimalDateOfDeath
Columns.Description: The date that the animal died.

Columns.Name: AnimalDateOfSlaughter
Columns.Description: The date that the animal was slaughtered.

Columns.Name: MarketAnimalIndicator
Columns.Description: Livestock bred and raised for food consumption

Columns.Name: CattleBreedId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a cattle breed.

Columns.Name: WeightAtBirthPounds
Columns.Description: The weight of the animal at birth.

Columns.Name: WeightAtSlaughterPounds
Columns.Description: The animal weight when slaughtered.

Columns.Name: CalvingIntervalDays
Columns.Description: Period between one calving and the next, usually 375 days.

Columns.Name: GestationPeriodDays
Columns.Description: Period from conception to parturition, average 283 days.

Columns.Name: PedigreeAnimalIndicator
Columns.Description:
Pedigree [Livestock General]
Pure bred animal registered with the breed society.

Columns.Name: CrossBreedAnimalIndicator
Columns.Description: Cross-breed is an animal that is a product of crossing two or more breeds. This is done to get the best facets of several breeds into one animal.

Columns.Name: CertifiedGrainfedIndicator
Columns.Description: Certified grainfed: Cattle sold with a statutory declaration to verify 70 days minimum at a registered feedlot.

Columns.Name: GrassFedAnimalIndicator
Columns.Description: An animal which has been fed on pasture (grass). Also used to describe the carcass when it is being sold.

Columns.Name: LongfedAnimalIndicator
Columns.Description: An animal that is grainfed, in a feedlot, for an extended period of time. Usually refers to cattle that are fed for over 200 days (up to 550 days) for the top Japanese markets. (See 'shortfed' and 'medium fed').

Columns.Name: LotfedAnimalIndicator
Columns.Description: An animal that is fed in a feedlot.

Columns.Name: PastureFedAnimalIndicator
Columns.Description: An animal that is grazed in a pasture.

Columns.Name: CarcassQualityGradeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a carcass quality grade.

Columns.Name: MeatQualityGradeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a meat quality grade.

Columns.Name: UsdaYieldGradeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a USDA Yield Grade.

Columns.Name: EstimatedBreedingValueId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an estimated breeding value.

Columns.Name: MuscleScoreId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a muscle score.

Columns.Name: BodyConditionScoreId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a body condition score.

Columns.Name: AnimalFrameSizeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an animal frame size.

Columns.Name: RfidTagId
Columns.Description:
The unique identifier of a RFID Tag.

The transmitter/receiver pair or transceiver plus the information storage mechanism attached to the object is referred to as the tag, transponder, electronic label, code plate and various other terms. 

Although transponder is technically the most accurate, the most common term and the one preferred by the Automatic Identification Manufacturers is tag.

Columns.Name: CattleTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a cattle type.
